items.name: Cocktail Meatballs
items.description: Cocktail meatballs are a classic for a reason. Instead of picking up some meatballs from the frozen section, this recipe starts from scratch.

items.name: Shrimp Cocktail Dip
items.description: Shrimp cocktail is a retro appetizer that we'll never stop loving, but even the best things can use a makeover every now and then! This savory dip is perfect for dinner parties.

items.name: Fig, Pecan, And Brie Bites
items.description: How pretty are these two-bite delights? They're the perfect way to use up the last of that puff pastry package sitting in your freezer.

items.name: Spicy Cheese Twists
items.description: This slightly upgraded version of cheese straws comes together with frozen puff pastry sheets. This approach is so easy, you will become committed to perfecting these puffy delights. Appetizers for dinner, anyone?

items.name: Cedar-Plank Salmon
items.description: The salmon takes on a light, smoky woodiness from grilling on a cedar plank, for a lovely pairing of earth and ocean.

items.name: Braised Chicken Legs With Grapes and Fennel
items.description: There's nothing wrong with defaulting to chicken when you're trying to think of dinner party ideas. The key is to select a truly special chicken recipe, like this easy sweet-and-spicy braise, made with ribbons of fennel and juicy table grapes. You'll want to have a loaf of bread on the side for sopping up the sauce.

items.name: Seared Scallops With Brown Butter and Lemon Pan Sauce
items.description: Scallops are always a stunner, but these are dead simple to make: Juice lemons. Spoon out capers. Heat pan. Cook scallops. Make sauce in same pan. Serve.

items.name: Classic Sole Meunière
items.description: This classic French dish frequently shows up in restaurants, but we promise that it's truly easy to pull off at home.

items.name: Grilled Okra, Corn, and Tomato Salad
items.description: Chef Vishwesh Bhatt turns heads with this summer salad's punchy charred jalapeño–and-herb-spiked dressing and palate-perking topping of toasted crunchy coriander and cumin seeds.

items.name: Sugar Snap Pea Salad
items.description: At Branch Line in Boston, Ivan Conill makes this light summer salad with sweet sugar snap peas, whole milk ricotta, and shredded rotisserie chicken.

items.name: Strawberry Burrata Salad
items.description: Creamy burrata is the centerpiece of this salad of strawberries marinated in a honey and balsamic vinaigrette and served over arugula and basil leaves. Toasted pine nuts add a little nutty crunch. Serve the salad as a main course for lunch or as a starter for dinner. Slices of crostini are perfect for scooping up the rich burrata and tangy berries.

items.name: Wedge Salad with Tahini Green Goddess Dressing
items.description: This crispy and refreshing wedge salad swaps standard blue cheese dressing for a bold and thick herb-forward green goddess made from mayo and sour cream. The secret to Justin Chapple’s spin on the dressing is tahini, which adds depth, nuttiness, and a pleasantly bitter edge.

items.name: Fresh tomato soup
items.description: This rich and creamy Dutch tomato soup, made with very ripe plum or vine tomatoes, was inspired by the delicious bowl of tomato soup served at Café de Jaren in Amsterdam.

items.name: Chicken and rice soup
items.description: Packed with protein and low in sugar, this chicken and rice soup is the perfect balance of hearty and healthy. Cooking the chicken and rice in a flavourful broth not only enhances the taste but keeps the chicken irresistibly tender.

items.name: Get-your-greens soup
items.description: Loaded with green veg and potato for creaminess, this immune-supportive soup needs just a splash of cream to become a hearty, warming lunch.

items.name: Chicken noodle soup
items.description: This slurp-able bowl of spicy coconut noodles with chicken was inspired by classic Thai red curry. The freshness of the DIY curry paste will help ward off any winter blues.

items.name: Magic Cheesecake Bars
items.description: Get your sweet tooth ready for a decadent cheesecake bar experience. These magic cheesecake bars are the best iteration of any cheesecake dessert (or any magic cookie bars) with a buttery graham cracker bottom, chocolate chip bits intertwined in rich cheesecake, and topped with toasted coconut and walnuts.

items.name: Ice Cream In A Bag
items.description: Pssst: You don't need a fancy ice cream maker to make ice cream at home, all you need is a plastic baggie and 15 minutes! Add a different extract, throw in a little chocolate syrup, or top with candy for the sundae of your dreams.

items.name: Chocolate Pie Cookies
items.description: If you love the richness and the comfort of homemade French silk pie, then these chocolate pie cookies are just what you need. Inspired by the classic, but with the ease and convenience of a cookie, this recipe offers a unique twist on beloved flavors.

items.name: Biscoff Trifle
items.description: You may be most familiar with these cookies as a beloved Delta in-flight snack. In fact, Biscoff’s partnership with the airline is what first introduced American consumers to the cookie in the 1980s. We love eating them all year long. So we decided to celebrate speculoos with this show-stopping holiday trifle.

items.name: Creamy Hot Cocoa
items.description: This cozy hot chocolate is so comforting on a dreary day. It makes the kitchen smell wonderful and it's good for the soul.

items.name: Mixed Berry Sangria
items.description: This is a light, tasty beverage to serve with spoons so everyone can enjoy the fresh berries once the sangria is gone. — Linda Cifuentes, Mahomet, Illinois

items.name: Watermelon Punch for a Crowd
items.description: How pretty are these two-bite delights? They're the perfect way to use up the last of that puff pastry package sitting in your freezer.

items.name: Lemony Fruit Cooler
items.description: This punch looks so pretty with all the colorful fruit floating in the bowl. It has a refreshing taste and is easy to put together. —Dawn Shackelford, Fort Worth, Texas

items.name: Savory Party Bread
items.description: It’s impossible to stop nibbling on warm pieces of this cheesy, oniony bread. The sliced loaf fans out for a fun presentation. It’s one of the best savory appetizers I’ve found. —Kay Daly, Raleigh, North Carolina

items.name: Teriyaki Pineapple Meatballs
items.description: These teriyaki pineapple meatballs appetizer changed so many times because of my family’s suggestions that it eventually became a main course. I think the homemade sauce sets these meatballs apart. —Evette Nowicki, Oak Harbor, Washington

items.name: Fruit Charcuterie Board
items.description: Who says cheese and sausage get to have all the fun? Make this fruit charcuterie board a party go-to with any that are in season. —Taste of Home Test Kitchen

items.name: Hot Spinach Artichoke Dip
items.description: One taste of this outrageously delicious hot spinach artichoke dip and your guests will not stop eating it until it’s gone. The savory blend of artichokes, spinach and Parmesan cheese is positively addictive! It tastes even better if you make it the night before and chill it in the fridge before baking. —Michelle Krzmarzick, Torrance, California

items.name: CHICKEN TRAYBAKE WITH GARLIC AND CHERRY TOMATOES
items.description: Remove the tray from the oven and scatter over the basil leaves. Let everyone help themselves to this very easy and super-tasty traybake.

items.name: Braised Chicken Legs With Grapes and Fennel
items.description: There's nothing wrong with defaulting to chicken when you're trying to think of dinner party ideas. The key is to select a truly special chicken recipe, like this easy sweet-and-spicy braise, made with ribbons of fennel and juicy table grapes. You'll want to have a loaf of bread on the side for sopping up the sauce.

items.name: ONGLET STEAK WITH GREEN PEPPERCORN SAUCE
items.description: Onglet steak is prized for its great flavour, but you’ll need to time the cooking carefully as it can become tough if overdone.

items.name: Spicy Pork Burgers with Romanesco Salsa
items.description: This Spanish-inspired pork burger is topped with smoky Romanesco salsa instead of ketchup, and slices of Manchego cheese.

items.name: Shaved Beet and Carrot Salad with Citrus-Scallion Dressing
items.description: When salad greens become scarce in late fall, try making this gorgeous, colorful salad of thinly shaved beets, carrot ribbons, and rounds of juicy clementine, served atop arugula and dressed with a citrus-scallion vinaigrette. Topped with nutty almonds, it's special enough to serve as part of a large feast and just as delicious as a quick, light lunch.

items.name: Arugula-Fennel Salad
items.description: Eugenia Bone, prolific home cook, writer, and author of Well-Preserved, always serves this simple green salad with Taleggio and aged Parmigiano-Reggiano, as well as fresh imported sheep's milk ricotta when it's available at the market.

items.name: Roasted Hot Honey Sweet Potato Salad
items.description: This sweet potato salad makes a colorful, satisfying side dish. Seasoning the potatoes with smoked paprika creates a sweet and savory balance while the hot honey dressing adds a touch of tangy heat. Homemade pickled red onions, crunchy toasted pecans, and fresh parsley round the dish out.

items.name: Goi Ga (Crunchy Vietnamese Chicken Salad)
items.description: Seattle restaurateurs Eric and Sophie Banh like to poach the chicken for this vibrant dish, then toss the salad with homemade scallion oil. To save time, use store-bought rotisserie chicken and skip the scallion oil; the salad gets plenty of flavor from the spicy, vinegary dressing and abundance of fresh herbs.

items.name: Herb Garden Matzo Ball Soup
items.description: Matzo ball soup gets a glow-up in this version by cookbook author Leah Koenig, with fresh parsley, dill, chives, and fennel fronds in the matzo balls themselves, plus more herbs, lemon zest, and edible flowers adding color and bright, spring flavors to each finished bowl of soup.

items.name: Mushroom-Chickpea Pozole
items.description: Here I use mushrooms to give us that earthy heartiness that you expect from pozole, no meat needed,' says chef Marcela Valladolid. 'Guajillo, ancho, and árbol chiles are soaked and pureed for a perfectly balanced sauce that punches up the savory mushroom broth; the chickpeas are a yummy twist in place of the dried hominy.

items.name: Shrimp Bisque
items.description: Sautéed shrimp shells impart a sweet complexity to the foundation of this deeply flavorful bisque. White rice is slowly simmered in the aromatic broth and then pureed to give the soup body and a velvety consistency, without masking the flavor of succulent shrimp. Serve with chopped steamed shrimp and a crusty baguette.

items.name: Manhattan Clam Chowder
items.description: This recipe for Manhattan Clam Chowder — known for being tomato-forward with a broth base — has layers of flavor, from the clam broth spiked with white wine to the tender vegetables that are cooked in bacon fat. Half of the clams are roughly chopped, while the other half are left whole in their shells for contrast.

items.name: Frosted Sugar Cookie Bars
items.description: Frosted sugar cookie bars are everything you love about a big, soft, frosted sugar cookie, in an easy

items.name: No bake cheesecake
items.description: This is a No Bake Cheesecake that tastes very similar to a classic Baked Cheesecake, made without the fuss of baking! It boasts an exceptionally smooth, light-yet-creamy filling and a buttery, crumbly crust that everybody is mad for.

items.name: Affogato
items.description: Affogato – coffee, dessert and your after dinner drink, all rolled into one. This is what you have when you’re “too full for dessert”! Just pour espresso coffee over vanilla gelato or ice cream, enjoy the melty swirls and dig in. The Italians are genius.

items.name: Mini Pavlovas
items.description: Mini Pavlovas are the individual version of traditional Pavlova. A delicate crisp meringue shell with fluffy marshmallow-y insides, they’re adorable, easier to make, and a lot less messy to serve! BONUS: you get the whole thing to yourself.

items.name: Mango Juice
items.description: mango juice recipe uses organic Alphonso mangoes for a terrifically sweet, nectar-like drink. Follow our step-by-step instructions with photos to learn how to make a delicious juice that’s perfect for enjoying by the glassful or including in any number of juice-based beverage recipes.

items.name: Berry Explosion Juice
items.description: This 'berry'delicious recipe combines an all-star lineup of berries with watermelon, pomegranate and mint. An antioxidant (and flavor) powerhouse juice.

items.name: Hot Chocolate
items.description: Creamy Homemade Hot Chocolate. A combination of cocoa powder and chocolate chips make this hot chocolate extra flavorful and delicious! Ready in minutes.

items.name: Red Velvet Cookie Cocktail
items.description: Try this luscious dessert cocktail as the perfect finish to your next dinner party. Cake-flavored vodka and red velvet cookies turn ice cream into a spectacular grownup treat.

items.name: Turkey Sliders with Sesame Slaw
items.description: I’m a fan of sliders, especially if they are Asian inspired. Sweet Hawaiian rolls make these especially tasty. —Gloria Bradley, Naperville, Illinois

items.name: Buffalo Chicken Dip
items.description: It is creamy, cheesy and packed with Buffalo hot wing flavors. This easy Buffalo chicken dip recipe is sure to be a party hit.

items.name: Pinwheels
items.description: Tortilla pinwheels are a crowd-pleasing, classic party food. Plus, the recipe is endlessly versatile!

items.name: Olives and Cheese
items.description: This elegant marinated olives and cheese platter is a perfect appetizer for any occasion, especially one with an Italian-inspired menu. The arrangement is visually appealing and temptingly delicious, and it can be made entirely ahead of time.

items.name: LAMB KOFTAS
items.description: love cooking lamb mince on the grill. It’s quite high in fat so the koftas won’t dry out and they crisp up wonderfully on the surface.

items.name: HERBY LEMON CHICKEN THIGHS
items.description: A real taste of the Mediterranean, with fresh herbs, extra virgin olive oil and a citrusy tang from preserved lemons.

items.name: STICKY PORK CHOPS
items.description: Sticky chops with great American smoky flavours, perfect with a fresh and crunchy slaw.

items.name: CHICKEN AND PRAWN GUMBO
items.description: It’s not a complicated gumbo recipe. It’s just full of ﬂavour, so give it a go

items.name: Caesar Salad with Greek-Style Yogurt Dressing
items.description: Chef Jamie Oliver makes his Caesar salad dressing with thick Greek-style yogurt, which he often uses as a less rich alternative to heavy cream and sour cream.

items.name: Big Italian Salad
items.description: Part green salad, part antipasto salad, this recipe combines lettuce, celery, onion, peperoncini, olives, and cherry tomatoes — all tossed in a dressing made with olive oil, vinegar, and a little mayonnaise.

items.name: Greek Salad
items.description: Cool and crunchy, this Greek salad with crispy cucumbers, juicy tomatoes, briny olives, and creamy feta cheese is the perfect summer meal. With just a handful of ingredients, it’s quick and effortless to assemble.

items.name: Double Ginger Salad with Chickpeas and Peanuts
items.description: Inspired by the salads at Burma Superstar in San Francisco and Mister Mao in New Orleans, punchy and crispy slaw-like salad gets its piquancy from a combination of fresh and pickled ginger. Fresh cilantro and spicy jalapeño echo the bright flavors of ginger, while peanuts, sesame seeds, and fried garlic and chickpeas add crunch and deep, nutty flavors.

items.name: Broccoli and Potato Soup
items.description: The bright green broccoli florets floating on top of this hearty soup make it especially eye-catching, but it's the broccoli stems that do the real work. They're cooked with the potatoes and then pureed to form a creamy base. A final sprinkle of grated Parmesan cheese gives the soup an extra savory touch.

items.name: Fire-Roasted Pasta e Fagioli
items.description: Pasta e fagioli (literally, “pasta and beans”) is a traditional Italian soup beloved for its hearty nature. This version has all the vegetables, pasta, and beans you expect from the classic dish, plus fire-roasted flavor from charred tomatoes and peppers.

items.name: Chicken Soup with Ginger and Cilantro
items.description: Here, quick-cooking boneless chicken pieces are gently simmered in a ginger and cilantro-infused broth with a dash of soy sauce. The eye-catching garnish tray doubles as a colorful centerpiece, allowing guests to pile their bowls with aromatic fresh herbs, spicy chiles, and juicy citrus.

items.name: Avgolemono Chicken Soup with Rice
items.description: Avgolemono is a classic sauce of chicken broth, egg yolks, and lemon juice in Turkish, Balkan, Arab, Greek, and some Jewish cuisines; the addition of a bit more broth, rice, and shredded chicken turns it into a satisfying soup.

items.name: Chocolate Mousse Cake
items.description: This incredible chocolate mousse cake is made with a tender chocolate cake, topped with creamy chocolate mousse, and a chocolate ganache shell.

items.name: Strawberry Swirl Cheesecake
items.description: This creamy and decadent strawberry swirl cheesecake is easy, fresh, and delicious, and is made without a water bath.

items.name: Chouquettes
items.description: These easy and delicious chouquettes are small French pastries made with airy Choux pastry, and coated with crunchy pearl sugar.

items.name: Crepe Cake
items.description: This crepe cake recipe is made by layering French crepes with whipped cream and topped with a delicious chocolate ganache.

items.name: Nectarine, Basil and Clementine Infused Water
items.description: Nectarine and basil may sound a little strange, but trust us, this combination is a real winner. A few slices of clementine seal the deal. —Taste of Home Test Kitchen

items.name: Honeydew Lime Cooler
items.description: Serve up a frosty glass of this citrusy blend of lime sherbet and honeydew melon for a real thirst-quencher. I like to sip this on warm afternoons, but it's equally good for breakfast or brunch. —Mitzi Sentiff, Annapolis, Maryland

items.name: Orange Dream Mimosas
items.description: Your inner child will love this fun riff on the classic mimosa. Use sparkling cider, ginger ale or sparkling grape juice for a nonalcoholic version. —Deirdre Cox, Kansas City, Missouri

items.name: Rhubarb Lemonade Slush
items.description: My family loves rhubarb, and this is such a fun way to enjoy it. It's nice to have in the freezer and bring out when guests drop by. Even people who aren't crazy about rhubarb enjoy it. —Cathie Beard, Philomath, Oregon

items.name: Almond-Bacon Cheese Crostini
items.description: For a change from the usual toasted tomato appetizer, try this baked crostini recipe. If you like, slice the baguette at an angle instead of making a straight cut. —Leondre Hermann, Stuart, Florida

items.name: Stuffed Cherry Tomatoes
items.description: Cream-cheese-stuffed cherry tomatoes are a simple yet delicious vegetarian appetizer that's an excellent accompaniment to a party spread of charcuterie and crudités.

items.name: Florentine Ciabatta
items.description: I came up with this appetizer because of my love for white pizza. I’ve served my ciabatta pizza at many holiday parties, and it’s always a big hit among both children and adults. —Noreen McCormick Danek, Cromwell, Connecticut

items.name: Party Shrimp
items.description: The marinade for this dish makes the shrimp so flavorful, you won't even need a dipping sauce. Even those who claim they don’t like shellfish really dig this appetizer. —Kendra Doss, Colorado Springs, Colorado

items.name: LEMON PEPPER CHICKEN WITH GREEN PEPPER SALSA
items.description: Lemon pepper chicken is one of those retro dishes that withstands the test of time because they taste good!

items.name: HERBY LEMON CHICKEN THIGHS
items.description: A real taste of the Mediterranean, with fresh herbs, extra virgin olive oil and a citrusy tang from preserved lemons.

items.name: SQUID AND CHORIZO SKEWERS
items.description: For a taste of Spanish holidays, charred squid is paired with Padrón peppers and spicy chorizo. Delicious!

items.name: BEEF SUYA SKEWERS
items.description: West African-inspired, with a spicy peanut mix that coats the beef skewers.

items.name: Salmon Niçoise 'Salad
items.description: Tender salmon, briny olives, crisp-tender green beans, and satisfying potatoes all soak up the zippy, perfectly balanced dressing in this variation on a classic tuna Niçoise. Don't skip the anchovy garnish — it provides pops of umami saltiness that take this salad over the top.

items.name: Kale Salad with Cranberries, Almonds, and Goat Cheese
items.description: This hearty kale salad with dried cranberries, sliced almonds, and fresh goat cheese is a wonderful, 15-minute side dish from food writer Emily Farris.

items.name: Citrus, Beet, and Arugula Salad with Halloumi Croutons
items.description: Food writer and cook Adeena Sussman crafts this peppery arugula salad with mixed citrus, jewel-toned roasted beets, and crispy halloumi croutons.

items.name: Grilled Onion Lyonnaise
items.description: This riff on a classic salade Lyonnaise takes the iconic salad from great to even greater. The finished salad of frisée; crisp, meaty bacon lardons; grilled red torpedo onions; and a mustard vinaigrette is topped with poached eggs.

items.name: Creamy Shrimp and Crab Bisque
items.description: Creamy, velvety, and absolutely delicious, this Creamy Shrimp and Crab Bisque is much easier than it looks: It only takes about 20 minutes to throw together.

items.name: Chef John's Gazpacho
items.description: There's nothing like cooling gazpacho on a warm summer night. Only use the sweetest end-of-season tomatoes for this one, warns Chef John. Anything else just won't do.

items.name: French Onion Soup Gratinee
items.description: Here, quick-cooking boneless chicken pieces are gently simmered in a ginger and cilantro-infused broth with a dash of soy sauce. The eye-catching garnish tray doubles as a colorful centerpiece, allowing guests to pile their bowls with aromatic fresh herbs, spicy chiles, and juicy citrus.

items.name: Chef John's Cassoulet
items.description: This classic French dish, which falls somewhere between soup and casserole, is a labor of love — but it's seriously worth the effort.

items.name: Coffee Cheesecake
items.description: This coffee cheesecake is made with an Oreo crust, filled with coffee cheesecake filling, topped with chocolate ganache, and coffee whipped cream.

items.name: 6. Boston Cream Donuts
items.description: These Boston cream donuts are made with fluffy yeast dough, filled with creamy vanilla custard, and topped with chocolate ganache.

items.name: Tiramisu Cookies
items.description: These tiramisu cookies are made with soft and chewy coffee cookies topped with creamy mascarpone cream, and topped with cocoa powder.

items.name: Apple Crumble Cheesecake
items.description: This apple crumble cheesecake is made with a creamy cheesecake filled with apple pie filling, topped with crumble topping and caramel sauce.

items.name: Strawberry-Lavender Infused Water
items.description: A little bit of lavender goes a long way, so be sure not to overdo it! This pretty combo screams summer, but you can also dry out the lavender and enjoy this anytime.

items.name: Guava Coconut Rum Cocktail
items.description: My beverage is so sensational it's like a taste of the tropics in a glass. The guava adds a touch of sweetness to this coconut drink. —Melanie Milhorat, New York, New York

items.name: Watermelon Spritzer
items.description: It couldn’t get much easier than this bright spritzer! Watermelon blended with limeade is cool and refreshing. It’s a wonderful thirst-quencher on a hot summer day. —Geraldine Saucier, Albuquerque, New Mexico

items.name: Rhubarb Lemonade Slush
items.description: My family loves rhubarb, and this is such a fun way to enjoy it. It's nice to have in the freezer and bring out when guests drop by. Even people who aren't crazy about rhubarb enjoy it. —Cathie Beard, Philomath, Oregon

items.name: German Beer Cheese Spread
items.description: We love recipes inspired by our German heritage. This tangy spread is fantastic served alongside everything, including pretzels and pumpernickel or crackers and sausage. Choose your favorite beer—the flavor really comes through. —Angela Spengler, Tampa, Florida

items.name: Mediterranean Hummus Nachos
items.description: My husband once piled all the Middle Eastern dishes I'd made on top of pita chips. It was delicious and fun, so we've kept doing it! We love this combination with ground lamb, too. I am half Lebanese, so we usually call these Lebanese nachos. Whatever you call them, you can't help but like them! —Gina Fensler, Cincinnati, Ohio

items.name: Crispy Sriracha Spring Rolls
items.description: While in the Bahamas, friends suggested a restaurant that served amazing chicken spring rolls. When I got home, I created my own version. Such a great appetizer to have waiting in the freezer! —Carla Mendres, Winnipeg, Manitoba

items.name: Cheesy Skillet Pizza Dip
items.description: This creamy dip is oozing with cheesy goodness thanks to the combination of cream cheese and mozzarella. We topped ours with pepperoni slices, but you can easily customize it with your favorite pizza toppings. This is just one more delicious way to use your cast-iron pan. —Taste of Home Test Kitchen, Milwaukee, Wisconsin

items.name: SLOW ROASTED LAMB WITH BOULANGÈRE POTATOES
items.description: I think I can safely call it the ultimate family lunch! ,SLOW ROASTED LAMB WITH BOULANGÈRE POTATOES

items.name: SLOW-ROASTED DUCK WITH POTATO PANCAKES
items.description: Everybody loves slow-roasted, crispy duck from a Chinese takeaway, but this is an English version for a more substantial main course.

items.name: CHICKEN WITH ROASTED CAULIFLOWER
items.description: Full of flavour and with a great texture, roast cauliflower is the ideal partner for roast chicken.

items.name: GAMMON STEAKS AND FRIED DUCK EGGS
items.description: This is a smartened up version of the ham-and-egg teas of my childhood.

items.name: Neoclassic Seafood Salad
items.description: This playful take on frutti di mare from legendary New York chef and restaurateur Alfred Portale showcases lobster, scallops, squid, and mussels with a showstopping presentation, just like at Gotham Bar and Grill.

items.name: Grilled Chicken Salad With Herby Tahini Dressing
items.description: Recipe developer Marianne Williams uses za’atar seasoning and Dijon mustard to infuse both the marinade and tahini dressing with herby, tangy flavor, while honey and lemon juice balance everything out. Crunchy Little Gem lettuce, sweet snap peas, peppery radishes, and cooling cucumber bring in lots of texture and flavor to this main course salad with make-ahead components.

items.name: Celery Salad with Calabrian Chile and Sunflower Seed Vinaigrette
items.description: This apple and celery salad from 2018 F&W Best New Chef Julia Sullivan of Henrietta Red in Nashville is spicy, sweet, fresh, and delicious. Nutty sunflower seed kernels round out each zippy bite.

items.name: Spinach, Grapefruit, and Avocado Salad with Sesame Vinaigrette
items.description: Toasted sesame oil adds depth to this light, 15-minute salad that showcases spring produce.

items.name: Tonkotsu Ramen
items.description: A slow-simmered, savory tonkotsu broth is the base to this ramen, which is rich from the meltingly tender chashu pork and soft-boiled egg and brightened by pickled mushrooms.

items.name: Smoked Ham Hock and Lentil Soup
items.description: The ham hock aroma hangs around the kitchen beautifully; the smell alone makes you warmer. Adding a little ginger and lemongrass

items.name: Chicken and Wild Rice Soup
items.description: Chicken and Wild Rice Soup

items.name: Pollo Guisado
items.description: 2019 F&W Best New Chef Kwame Onwuachi says this comforting recipe is 'the soup all abuelitas make their grandchildren, cooking a ojo, or by feel, with a million variations.'

items.name: Tiramisu Cups
items.description: These individual tiramisu cups are an easy twist on the classic dessert, made with layers of creamy mascarpone, ladyfingers, and cocoa powder, this makes the perfect dessert!

items.name: Mango Mousse
items.description: This incredibly delicious mango mousse has a smooth and creamy texture and a sweet and tangy taste of fresh mangoes.

items.name: Creme Brulee Cheesecake
items.description: This creme brulee cheesecake is creamy, thick, and custardy, made with a graham cracker crust, and topped with a burnt caramel shell on top, just like creme brulee!

items.name: Chocolate Ganache Cake
items.description: This chocolate ganache cake is made with moist and rich chocolate cake, filled with chocolate ganache, frosted with whipped chocolate ganache, and topped with a chocolate drip.

items.name: Raspberry and Lemon Infused Water
items.description: If you're craving raspberry lemonade but are trying to cut back on your sugar intake, this infused water is the perfect substitute.—James Schend, Pleasant Prairie, Wisconsin

items.name: Watermelon Mojito
items.description: We added watermelon to the classic mojito recipe for an extra sweet (and pink!) spin on the classic Cuban cocktail. —Taste of Home Test Kitchen

items.name: Tropical Cooler
items.description: With only four simple ingredients, this refreshing punch is easy to stir up in just 10 minutes. I served it at a party for my son, and everyone liked the slightly tart flavor. —Robin Werner, Brush Prairie, Washington

items.name: Strawberry Melon Fizz
items.description: Experimenting in the kitchen is fun for me. I came up with this recipe by I combining two different recipes, one for a melon ball basket and another for a sparkling beverage. —Teresa Messick, Montgomery, Alabama

items.name: Pepperoni Bread
items.description: Our contest-winning pepperoni bread recipe begins with frozen bread dough, so there's no need to make your own dough. Simply thaw it, roll it out and stuff it with cheese, pepperoni and other savory delights like olives, mushrooms and pickled peppers.

items.name: Spicy Sweet Potato Chips & Cilantro Dip
items.description: This irresistible combo could become your new signature snack food. Park the spicy baked chips next to a bowl of the cool, creamy dip and let the gang have at it. What a fantastic twist on traditional chips and dip! —Elizabeth Godecke, Chicago, Illinois

items.name: Sausage Cream Cheese Dip
items.description: This scrumptious snack will go fast! The sausage cream cheese dip recipe is so easy to make and fits Southwestern flavor to a T. My pot is always scraped clean! —Kaye Christiansen, Freistatt, Missouri

items.name: Antipasto Platter
items.description: A bold and effortless mix of savory meats, tangy cheese and crisp vegetables, this antipasto platter is the ultimate go-to for an easy and crowd-pleasing appetizer.

items.name: RIBEYE STEAK CHASSEUR
items.description: The crumble topping lends that all-important crunch that compliments rich flavour and robust texture.

items.name: PIRI PIRI CHICKEN WITH LITTLE GEM SALAD
items.description: Who doesn’t love piri piri chicken? This is such a great recipe, a real favourite of mine for when that hot, hot chicken craving hits.

items.name: Pineapple-Coconut Smoothie
items.description: Use fresh or frozen fruits in this coconutty recipe. It's like a pina colada, but better for you and more versatile. —Gunjan Dudani, Bellevue, Washington

items.name: Cocktail Meatballs
items.description: Cocktail meatballs are a classic for a reason. Instead of picking up some meatballs from the frozen section, this recipe starts from scratch.

items.name: Shrimp Cocktail Dip
items.description: Shrimp cocktail is a retro appetizer that we'll never stop loving, but even the best things can use a makeover every now and then! This savory dip is perfect for dinner parties.

items.name: Fig, Pecan, And Brie Bites
items.description: How pretty are these two-bite delights? They're the perfect way to use up the last of that puff pastry package sitting in your freezer.

items.name: Spicy Cheese Twists
items.description: This slightly upgraded version of cheese straws comes together with frozen puff pastry sheets. This approach is so easy, you will become committed to perfecting these puffy delights. Appetizers for dinner, anyone?

items.name: Cedar-Plank Salmon
items.description: The salmon takes on a light, smoky woodiness from grilling on a cedar plank, for a lovely pairing of earth and ocean.

items.name: Braised Chicken Legs With Grapes and Fennel
items.description: There's nothing wrong with defaulting to chicken when you're trying to think of dinner party ideas. The key is to select a truly special chicken recipe, like this easy sweet-and-spicy braise, made with ribbons of fennel and juicy table grapes. You'll want to have a loaf of bread on the side for sopping up the sauce.

items.name: Seared Scallops With Brown Butter and Lemon Pan Sauce
items.description: Scallops are always a stunner, but these are dead simple to make: Juice lemons. Spoon out capers. Heat pan. Cook scallops. Make sauce in same pan. Serve.

items.name: Classic Sole Meunière
items.description: This classic French dish frequently shows up in restaurants, but we promise that it's truly easy to pull off at home.

items.name: Grilled Okra, Corn, and Tomato Salad
items.description: Chef Vishwesh Bhatt turns heads with this summer salad's punchy charred jalapeño–and-herb-spiked dressing and palate-perking topping of toasted crunchy coriander and cumin seeds.

items.name: Sugar Snap Pea Salad
items.description: At Branch Line in Boston, Ivan Conill makes this light summer salad with sweet sugar snap peas, whole milk ricotta, and shredded rotisserie chicken.

items.name: Strawberry Burrata Salad
items.description: Creamy burrata is the centerpiece of this salad of strawberries marinated in a honey and balsamic vinaigrette and served over arugula and basil leaves. Toasted pine nuts add a little nutty crunch. Serve the salad as a main course for lunch or as a starter for dinner. Slices of crostini are perfect for scooping up the rich burrata and tangy berries.

items.name: Wedge Salad with Tahini Green Goddess Dressing
items.description: This crispy and refreshing wedge salad swaps standard blue cheese dressing for a bold and thick herb-forward green goddess made from mayo and sour cream. The secret to Justin Chapple’s spin on the dressing is tahini, which adds depth, nuttiness, and a pleasantly bitter edge.

items.name: Fresh tomato soup
items.description: This rich and creamy Dutch tomato soup, made with very ripe plum or vine tomatoes, was inspired by the delicious bowl of tomato soup served at Café de Jaren in Amsterdam.

items.name: Chicken and rice soup
items.description: Packed with protein and low in sugar, this chicken and rice soup is the perfect balance of hearty and healthy. Cooking the chicken and rice in a flavourful broth not only enhances the taste but keeps the chicken irresistibly tender.

items.name: Get-your-greens soup
items.description: Loaded with green veg and potato for creaminess, this immune-supportive soup needs just a splash of cream to become a hearty, warming lunch.

items.name: Chicken noodle soup
items.description: This slurp-able bowl of spicy coconut noodles with chicken was inspired by classic Thai red curry. The freshness of the DIY curry paste will help ward off any winter blues.

items.name: Magic Cheesecake Bars
items.description: Get your sweet tooth ready for a decadent cheesecake bar experience. These magic cheesecake bars are the best iteration of any cheesecake dessert (or any magic cookie bars) with a buttery graham cracker bottom, chocolate chip bits intertwined in rich cheesecake, and topped with toasted coconut and walnuts.

items.name: Ice Cream In A Bag
items.description: Pssst: You don't need a fancy ice cream maker to make ice cream at home, all you need is a plastic baggie and 15 minutes! Add a different extract, throw in a little chocolate syrup, or top with candy for the sundae of your dreams.

items.name: Chocolate Pie Cookies
items.description: If you love the richness and the comfort of homemade French silk pie, then these chocolate pie cookies are just what you need. Inspired by the classic, but with the ease and convenience of a cookie, this recipe offers a unique twist on beloved flavors.

items.name: Biscoff Trifle
items.description: You may be most familiar with these cookies as a beloved Delta in-flight snack. In fact, Biscoff’s partnership with the airline is what first introduced American consumers to the cookie in the 1980s. We love eating them all year long. So we decided to celebrate speculoos with this show-stopping holiday trifle.

items.name: Creamy Hot Cocoa
items.description: This cozy hot chocolate is so comforting on a dreary day. It makes the kitchen smell wonderful and it's good for the soul.

items.name: Mixed Berry Sangria
items.description: This is a light, tasty beverage to serve with spoons so everyone can enjoy the fresh berries once the sangria is gone. — Linda Cifuentes, Mahomet, Illinois

items.name: Watermelon Punch for a Crowd
items.description: How pretty are these two-bite delights? They're the perfect way to use up the last of that puff pastry package sitting in your freezer.

items.name: Lemony Fruit Cooler
items.description: This punch looks so pretty with all the colorful fruit floating in the bowl. It has a refreshing taste and is easy to put together. —Dawn Shackelford, Fort Worth, Texas

items.name: Savory Party Bread
items.description: It’s impossible to stop nibbling on warm pieces of this cheesy, oniony bread. The sliced loaf fans out for a fun presentation. It’s one of the best savory appetizers I’ve found. —Kay Daly, Raleigh, North Carolina

items.name: Teriyaki Pineapple Meatballs
items.description: These teriyaki pineapple meatballs appetizer changed so many times because of my family’s suggestions that it eventually became a main course. I think the homemade sauce sets these meatballs apart. —Evette Nowicki, Oak Harbor, Washington

items.name: Fruit Charcuterie Board
items.description: Who says cheese and sausage get to have all the fun? Make this fruit charcuterie board a party go-to with any that are in season. —Taste of Home Test Kitchen

items.name: Hot Spinach Artichoke Dip
items.description: One taste of this outrageously delicious hot spinach artichoke dip and your guests will not stop eating it until it’s gone. The savory blend of artichokes, spinach and Parmesan cheese is positively addictive! It tastes even better if you make it the night before and chill it in the fridge before baking. —Michelle Krzmarzick, Torrance, California

items.name: CHICKEN TRAYBAKE WITH GARLIC AND CHERRY TOMATOES
items.description: Remove the tray from the oven and scatter over the basil leaves. Let everyone help themselves to this very easy and super-tasty traybake.

items.name: Braised Chicken Legs With Grapes and Fennel
items.description: There's nothing wrong with defaulting to chicken when you're trying to think of dinner party ideas. The key is to select a truly special chicken recipe, like this easy sweet-and-spicy braise, made with ribbons of fennel and juicy table grapes. You'll want to have a loaf of bread on the side for sopping up the sauce.

items.name: ONGLET STEAK WITH GREEN PEPPERCORN SAUCE
items.description: Onglet steak is prized for its great flavour, but you’ll need to time the cooking carefully as it can become tough if overdone.

items.name: Spicy Pork Burgers with Romanesco Salsa
items.description: This Spanish-inspired pork burger is topped with smoky Romanesco salsa instead of ketchup, and slices of Manchego cheese.

items.name: Shaved Beet and Carrot Salad with Citrus-Scallion Dressing
items.description: When salad greens become scarce in late fall, try making this gorgeous, colorful salad of thinly shaved beets, carrot ribbons, and rounds of juicy clementine, served atop arugula and dressed with a citrus-scallion vinaigrette. Topped with nutty almonds, it's special enough to serve as part of a large feast and just as delicious as a quick, light lunch.

items.name: Arugula-Fennel Salad
items.description: Eugenia Bone, prolific home cook, writer, and author of Well-Preserved, always serves this simple green salad with Taleggio and aged Parmigiano-Reggiano, as well as fresh imported sheep's milk ricotta when it's available at the market.

items.name: Roasted Hot Honey Sweet Potato Salad
items.description: This sweet potato salad makes a colorful, satisfying side dish. Seasoning the potatoes with smoked paprika creates a sweet and savory balance while the hot honey dressing adds a touch of tangy heat. Homemade pickled red onions, crunchy toasted pecans, and fresh parsley round the dish out.

items.name: Goi Ga (Crunchy Vietnamese Chicken Salad)
items.description: Seattle restaurateurs Eric and Sophie Banh like to poach the chicken for this vibrant dish, then toss the salad with homemade scallion oil. To save time, use store-bought rotisserie chicken and skip the scallion oil; the salad gets plenty of flavor from the spicy, vinegary dressing and abundance of fresh herbs.

items.name: Herb Garden Matzo Ball Soup
items.description: Matzo ball soup gets a glow-up in this version by cookbook author Leah Koenig, with fresh parsley, dill, chives, and fennel fronds in the matzo balls themselves, plus more herbs, lemon zest, and edible flowers adding color and bright, spring flavors to each finished bowl of soup.

items.name: Mushroom-Chickpea Pozole
items.description: Here I use mushrooms to give us that earthy heartiness that you expect from pozole, no meat needed,' says chef Marcela Valladolid. 'Guajillo, ancho, and árbol chiles are soaked and pureed for a perfectly balanced sauce that punches up the savory mushroom broth; the chickpeas are a yummy twist in place of the dried hominy.

items.name: Shrimp Bisque
items.description: Sautéed shrimp shells impart a sweet complexity to the foundation of this deeply flavorful bisque. White rice is slowly simmered in the aromatic broth and then pureed to give the soup body and a velvety consistency, without masking the flavor of succulent shrimp. Serve with chopped steamed shrimp and a crusty baguette.

items.name: Manhattan Clam Chowder
items.description: This recipe for Manhattan Clam Chowder — known for being tomato-forward with a broth base — has layers of flavor, from the clam broth spiked with white wine to the tender vegetables that are cooked in bacon fat. Half of the clams are roughly chopped, while the other half are left whole in their shells for contrast.

items.name: Frosted Sugar Cookie Bars
items.description: Frosted sugar cookie bars are everything you love about a big, soft, frosted sugar cookie, in an easy

items.name: No bake cheesecake
items.description: This is a No Bake Cheesecake that tastes very similar to a classic Baked Cheesecake, made without the fuss of baking! It boasts an exceptionally smooth, light-yet-creamy filling and a buttery, crumbly crust that everybody is mad for.

items.name: Affogato
items.description: Affogato – coffee, dessert and your after dinner drink, all rolled into one. This is what you have when you’re “too full for dessert”! Just pour espresso coffee over vanilla gelato or ice cream, enjoy the melty swirls and dig in. The Italians are genius.

items.name: Mini Pavlovas
items.description: Mini Pavlovas are the individual version of traditional Pavlova. A delicate crisp meringue shell with fluffy marshmallow-y insides, they’re adorable, easier to make, and a lot less messy to serve! BONUS: you get the whole thing to yourself.

items.name: Mango Juice
items.description: mango juice recipe uses organic Alphonso mangoes for a terrifically sweet, nectar-like drink. Follow our step-by-step instructions with photos to learn how to make a delicious juice that’s perfect for enjoying by the glassful or including in any number of juice-based beverage recipes.

items.name: Berry Explosion Juice
items.description: This 'berry'delicious recipe combines an all-star lineup of berries with watermelon, pomegranate and mint. An antioxidant (and flavor) powerhouse juice.

items.name: Hot Chocolate
items.description: Creamy Homemade Hot Chocolate. A combination of cocoa powder and chocolate chips make this hot chocolate extra flavorful and delicious! Ready in minutes.

items.name: Red Velvet Cookie Cocktail
items.description: Try this luscious dessert cocktail as the perfect finish to your next dinner party. Cake-flavored vodka and red velvet cookies turn ice cream into a spectacular grownup treat.

results.name: Horta Grand Café & Art Nouveau Zaal

items.name: Almond-Bacon Cheese Crostini
items.description: For a change from the usual toasted tomato appetizer, try this baked crostini recipe. If you like, slice the baguette at an angle instead of making a straight cut. —Leondre Hermann, Stuart, Florida

items.name: Stuffed Cherry Tomatoes
items.description: Cream-cheese-stuffed cherry tomatoes are a simple yet delicious vegetarian appetizer that's an excellent accompaniment to a party spread of charcuterie and crudités.

items.name: Florentine Ciabatta
items.description: I came up with this appetizer because of my love for white pizza. I’ve served my ciabatta pizza at many holiday parties, and it’s always a big hit among both children and adults. —Noreen McCormick Danek, Cromwell, Connecticut

items.name: Party Shrimp
items.description: The marinade for this dish makes the shrimp so flavorful, you won't even need a dipping sauce. Even those who claim they don’t like shellfish really dig this appetizer. —Kendra Doss, Colorado Springs, Colorado

items.name: LEMON PEPPER CHICKEN WITH GREEN PEPPER SALSA
items.description: Lemon pepper chicken is one of those retro dishes that withstands the test of time because they taste good!

items.name: HERBY LEMON CHICKEN THIGHS
items.description: A real taste of the Mediterranean, with fresh herbs, extra virgin olive oil and a citrusy tang from preserved lemons.

items.name: SQUID AND CHORIZO SKEWERS
items.description: For a taste of Spanish holidays, charred squid is paired with Padrón peppers and spicy chorizo. Delicious!

items.name: BEEF SUYA SKEWERS
items.description: West African-inspired, with a spicy peanut mix that coats the beef skewers.

items.name: Salmon Niçoise 'Salad
items.description: Tender salmon, briny olives, crisp-tender green beans, and satisfying potatoes all soak up the zippy, perfectly balanced dressing in this variation on a classic tuna Niçoise. Don't skip the anchovy garnish — it provides pops of umami saltiness that take this salad over the top.

items.name: Kale Salad with Cranberries, Almonds, and Goat Cheese
items.description: This hearty kale salad with dried cranberries, sliced almonds, and fresh goat cheese is a wonderful, 15-minute side dish from food writer Emily Farris.

items.name: Citrus, Beet, and Arugula Salad with Halloumi Croutons
items.description: Food writer and cook Adeena Sussman crafts this peppery arugula salad with mixed citrus, jewel-toned roasted beets, and crispy halloumi croutons.

items.name: Grilled Onion Lyonnaise
items.description: This riff on a classic salade Lyonnaise takes the iconic salad from great to even greater. The finished salad of frisée; crisp, meaty bacon lardons; grilled red torpedo onions; and a mustard vinaigrette is topped with poached eggs.

items.name: Creamy Shrimp and Crab Bisque
items.description: Creamy, velvety, and absolutely delicious, this Creamy Shrimp and Crab Bisque is much easier than it looks: It only takes about 20 minutes to throw together.

items.name: Chef John's Gazpacho
items.description: There's nothing like cooling gazpacho on a warm summer night. Only use the sweetest end-of-season tomatoes for this one, warns Chef John. Anything else just won't do.

items.name: French Onion Soup Gratinee
items.description: Here, quick-cooking boneless chicken pieces are gently simmered in a ginger and cilantro-infused broth with a dash of soy sauce. The eye-catching garnish tray doubles as a colorful centerpiece, allowing guests to pile their bowls with aromatic fresh herbs, spicy chiles, and juicy citrus.

items.name: Chef John's Cassoulet
items.description: This classic French dish, which falls somewhere between soup and casserole, is a labor of love — but it's seriously worth the effort.

items.name: Coffee Cheesecake
items.description: This coffee cheesecake is made with an Oreo crust, filled with coffee cheesecake filling, topped with chocolate ganache, and coffee whipped cream.

items.name: 6. Boston Cream Donuts
items.description: These Boston cream donuts are made with fluffy yeast dough, filled with creamy vanilla custard, and topped with chocolate ganache.

items.name: Tiramisu Cookies
items.description: These tiramisu cookies are made with soft and chewy coffee cookies topped with creamy mascarpone cream, and topped with cocoa powder.

items.name: Apple Crumble Cheesecake
items.description: This apple crumble cheesecake is made with a creamy cheesecake filled with apple pie filling, topped with crumble topping and caramel sauce.

items.name: Strawberry-Lavender Infused Water
items.description: A little bit of lavender goes a long way, so be sure not to overdo it! This pretty combo screams summer, but you can also dry out the lavender and enjoy this anytime.

items.name: Guava Coconut Rum Cocktail
items.description: My beverage is so sensational it's like a taste of the tropics in a glass. The guava adds a touch of sweetness to this coconut drink. —Melanie Milhorat, New York, New York

items.name: Watermelon Spritzer
items.description: It couldn’t get much easier than this bright spritzer! Watermelon blended with limeade is cool and refreshing. It’s a wonderful thirst-quencher on a hot summer day. —Geraldine Saucier, Albuquerque, New Mexico

items.name: Rhubarb Lemonade Slush
items.description: My family loves rhubarb, and this is such a fun way to enjoy it. It's nice to have in the freezer and bring out when guests drop by. Even people who aren't crazy about rhubarb enjoy it. —Cathie Beard, Philomath, Oregon

items.name: German Beer Cheese Spread
items.description: We love recipes inspired by our German heritage. This tangy spread is fantastic served alongside everything, including pretzels and pumpernickel or crackers and sausage. Choose your favorite beer—the flavor really comes through. —Angela Spengler, Tampa, Florida

items.name: Mediterranean Hummus Nachos
items.description: My husband once piled all the Middle Eastern dishes I'd made on top of pita chips. It was delicious and fun, so we've kept doing it! We love this combination with ground lamb, too. I am half Lebanese, so we usually call these Lebanese nachos. Whatever you call them, you can't help but like them! —Gina Fensler, Cincinnati, Ohio

items.name: Crispy Sriracha Spring Rolls
items.description: While in the Bahamas, friends suggested a restaurant that served amazing chicken spring rolls. When I got home, I created my own version. Such a great appetizer to have waiting in the freezer! —Carla Mendres, Winnipeg, Manitoba

items.name: Cheesy Skillet Pizza Dip
items.description: This creamy dip is oozing with cheesy goodness thanks to the combination of cream cheese and mozzarella. We topped ours with pepperoni slices, but you can easily customize it with your favorite pizza toppings. This is just one more delicious way to use your cast-iron pan. —Taste of Home Test Kitchen, Milwaukee, Wisconsin

items.name: SLOW ROASTED LAMB WITH BOULANGÈRE POTATOES
items.description: I think I can safely call it the ultimate family lunch! ,SLOW ROASTED LAMB WITH BOULANGÈRE POTATOES

items.name: SLOW-ROASTED DUCK WITH POTATO PANCAKES
items.description: Everybody loves slow-roasted, crispy duck from a Chinese takeaway, but this is an English version for a more substantial main course.

items.name: CHICKEN WITH ROASTED CAULIFLOWER
items.description: Full of flavour and with a great texture, roast cauliflower is the ideal partner for roast chicken.

items.name: GAMMON STEAKS AND FRIED DUCK EGGS
items.description: This is a smartened up version of the ham-and-egg teas of my childhood.

items.name: Neoclassic Seafood Salad
items.description: This playful take on frutti di mare from legendary New York chef and restaurateur Alfred Portale showcases lobster, scallops, squid, and mussels with a showstopping presentation, just like at Gotham Bar and Grill.

items.name: Grilled Chicken Salad With Herby Tahini Dressing
items.description: Recipe developer Marianne Williams uses za’atar seasoning and Dijon mustard to infuse both the marinade and tahini dressing with herby, tangy flavor, while honey and lemon juice balance everything out. Crunchy Little Gem lettuce, sweet snap peas, peppery radishes, and cooling cucumber bring in lots of texture and flavor to this main course salad with make-ahead components.

items.name: Celery Salad with Calabrian Chile and Sunflower Seed Vinaigrette
items.description: This apple and celery salad from 2018 F&W Best New Chef Julia Sullivan of Henrietta Red in Nashville is spicy, sweet, fresh, and delicious. Nutty sunflower seed kernels round out each zippy bite.

items.name: Spinach, Grapefruit, and Avocado Salad with Sesame Vinaigrette
items.description: Toasted sesame oil adds depth to this light, 15-minute salad that showcases spring produce.

items.name: Tonkotsu Ramen
items.description: A slow-simmered, savory tonkotsu broth is the base to this ramen, which is rich from the meltingly tender chashu pork and soft-boiled egg and brightened by pickled mushrooms.

items.name: Smoked Ham Hock and Lentil Soup
items.description: The ham hock aroma hangs around the kitchen beautifully; the smell alone makes you warmer. Adding a little ginger and lemongrass

items.description: Chicken and Wild Rice Soup

items.name: Pollo Guisado
items.description: 2019 F&W Best New Chef Kwame Onwuachi says this comforting recipe is 'the soup all abuelitas make their grandchildren, cooking a ojo, or by feel, with a million variations.'

items.name: Tiramisu Cups
items.description: These individual tiramisu cups are an easy twist on the classic dessert, made with layers of creamy mascarpone, ladyfingers, and cocoa powder, this makes the perfect dessert!

items.name: Mango Mousse
items.description: This incredibly delicious mango mousse has a smooth and creamy texture and a sweet and tangy taste of fresh mangoes.

items.name: Creme Brulee Cheesecake
items.description: This creme brulee cheesecake is creamy, thick, and custardy, made with a graham cracker crust, and topped with a burnt caramel shell on top, just like creme brulee!

items.name: Chocolate Ganache Cake
items.description: This chocolate ganache cake is made with moist and rich chocolate cake, filled with chocolate ganache, frosted with whipped chocolate ganache, and topped with a chocolate drip.

items.name: Raspberry and Lemon Infused Water
items.description: If you're craving raspberry lemonade but are trying to cut back on your sugar intake, this infused water is the perfect substitute.—James Schend, Pleasant Prairie, Wisconsin

items.name: Watermelon Mojito
items.description: We added watermelon to the classic mojito recipe for an extra sweet (and pink!) spin on the classic Cuban cocktail. —Taste of Home Test Kitchen

items.name: Tropical Cooler
items.description: With only four simple ingredients, this refreshing punch is easy to stir up in just 10 minutes. I served it at a party for my son, and everyone liked the slightly tart flavor. —Robin Werner, Brush Prairie, Washington

items.name: Strawberry Melon Fizz
items.description: Experimenting in the kitchen is fun for me. I came up with this recipe by I combining two different recipes, one for a melon ball basket and another for a sparkling beverage. —Teresa Messick, Montgomery, Alabama

items.name: Pepperoni Bread
items.description: Our contest-winning pepperoni bread recipe begins with frozen bread dough, so there's no need to make your own dough. Simply thaw it, roll it out and stuff it with cheese, pepperoni and other savory delights like olives, mushrooms and pickled peppers.

items.name: Spicy Sweet Potato Chips & Cilantro Dip
items.description: This irresistible combo could become your new signature snack food. Park the spicy baked chips next to a bowl of the cool, creamy dip and let the gang have at it. What a fantastic twist on traditional chips and dip! —Elizabeth Godecke, Chicago, Illinois

items.name: Sausage Cream Cheese Dip
items.description: This scrumptious snack will go fast! The sausage cream cheese dip recipe is so easy to make and fits Southwestern flavor to a T. My pot is always scraped clean! —Kaye Christiansen, Freistatt, Missouri

items.name: Antipasto Platter
items.description: A bold and effortless mix of savory meats, tangy cheese and crisp vegetables, this antipasto platter is the ultimate go-to for an easy and crowd-pleasing appetizer.

items.name: RIBEYE STEAK CHASSEUR
items.description: The crumble topping lends that all-important crunch that compliments rich flavour and robust texture.

items.name: PIRI PIRI CHICKEN WITH LITTLE GEM SALAD
items.description: Who doesn’t love piri piri chicken? This is such a great recipe, a real favourite of mine for when that hot, hot chicken craving hits.

items.name: LAMB SHANK HOT POT
items.description: Here I’ve recreated that old-school favourite, Lancashire hot pot, using a different cut of lamb.

items.name: MOROCCAN CHICKEN WITH CAULIFLOWER COUSCOUS
items.description: This dish is good warm or cold, so it’s ideal for a substantial packed lunch the next day too.

items.name: Dungeness Crab Salad
items.description: Ready in just over an hour, this abundant winter salad from Ali Ramee is as delicious as it is beautiful, with crisp greens, winter fruits, crunchy croutons, and fresh crabmeat.

items.name: Mission Fig, Elderberry, and Mixed Greens Salad
items.description: Winemaker Tara Gomez belongs to the Santa Ynez Band of Chumash Indians and runs the winery Camins 2 Dreams with her wife Mireia Taribó.

items.name: Crunchy Mango and Avocado Salad
items.description: Marve McClain combines Savoy and red cabbage, tender herbs, and crunchy cashews with a creamy lemon-ginger dressing in this colorful salad that's ready in a half hour.

items.name: Celery Salad with Pine Nuts, Arugula, Feta, and Pita
items.description: Celery gives this salad an anchoring earthy flavor accented by an herbaceous and lively dressing made from a few common kitchen acids like lemon juice and red wine vinegar.

items.name: Beef Bourguignon Without the Burgundy
items.description: We bet Julia Child would approve of this rich and flavorful recipe, which is made with merlot instead of the traditional Burgundy.

items.name: Cioppino
items.description: A wonderful seafood stew,'says recipe creator Star Pooley. 'Serve with a loaf of warm, crusty bread for sopping up the delicious broth!

items.name: Cream of Brie Soup
items.description: Sometimes you just want to eat a bowl of creamy cheese and butter — that's where this luxurious soup comes in.

items.name: Cream of Chicken and Gnocchi Soup
items.description: Why go out to get cream of chicken and gnocchi soup at a restaurant when you can make an even better version right at home? Community members recommend boiling the gnocchi before adding it to the soup so it's nice and tender.

items.name: Strawberry Tiramisu
items.description: This strawberry tiramisu is made with a delicious and creamy mascarpone strawberry filling, soft ladyfingers, and topped with fresh strawberries.

items.name: Limoncello Mascarpone Cake
items.description: This limoncello mascarpone cake has a soft and tender crumb and is topped with creamy mascarpone cream and lemon curd.

items.name: Chocolate Parfait
items.description: This chocolate parfait is made with layers of rich chocolate mousse, velvety whipped cream, and crunchy chocolate cookie crumbs.

items.name: Dark Chocolate Brownies
items.description: These dark chocolate brownies are fudgy and moist and are made with Dutch cocoa powder and high-quality dark chocolate.

items.name: Strawberry Mojito
items.description: Strawberries, lime and mint play so well together in this summery cocktail. Try it with any berry you have in the fridge! —Taste of Home Test Kitchen

items.name: Sparkling Rhubarb Spritzer
items.description: Folks with a rhubarb plant or two will love this recipe. It's a nice change from the usual lemonade—we enjoy it all summer long. —Sue Rebers, Campbellsport, Wisconsin

items.name: Apricot Lemonade Iced Tea
items.description: Every special occasion deserves a refreshing beverage (and a lovely punch bowl). Our tea has a tangy flavor from lemonade, apricot nectar and mint. —Kay Chon, Sherwood, Arkansas

items.name: Apricot Lemonade Iced Tea
items.description: Every special occasion deserves a refreshing beverage (and a lovely punch bowl). Our tea has a tangy flavor from lemonade, apricot nectar and mint. —Kay Chon, Sherwood, Arkansas

items.name: Taco Joe Dip
items.description: it’s perfect for parties or busy days. —Lang Secrest, Sierra Vista, Arizona

items.name: Slow-Cooker Buffalo Chicken Dip
items.description: If you like spice, you’ll love this slow-cooker Buffalo chicken dip. It’s super cheesy, full of rich flavor and really has that Buffalo wing taste! —Taste of Home Test Kitchen

items.name: Chicken Pot Stickers
items.description: Chicken and mushrooms make up the filling in these pot stickers, a traditional Chinese dumpling. Greasing the steamer rack makes it easier to remove them once they're steamed. —Jacquelynne Stine, Las Vegas, Nevada

items.name: Oven-Fried Oysters
items.description: I entered this recipe for breaded and baked oysters with a zippy jalapeno mayonnaise in a seafood contest and took first place in the hors d’oeuvres category. These oven-fried oysters make an interesting appetizer for entertaining. —Marie Rizzio, Interlochen, Michigan

items.name: SPICY CHILLI WITH GREEN BEANS
items.description: This is a real favourite in our house. It’s simple to make and layered with so many deliciously spicy flavours.

items.name: PAPRIKA ROAST RIB OF PORK
